-- Omron to Spend $38 Million Building China Electric Parts Plant in Shanghai
-- Adam Le
-- 2010-07-16T00:01:14Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-16/omron-to-spend-38-million-building-china-electric-parts-plant-in-shanghai.html

          
          
             Omron Corp. will spend 3.3 billion
yen ($38 million) to build a plant in Shanghai to double its
production capacity for relays and switches. Yasushi Kawamoto, a
spokesman for the Kyoto, western Japan-based company, said the
plant is expected to be completed by January 2012, confirming a
report in the Nikkan Kogyo newspaper.  
